==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anamorphosis
<hw>An`a*mor"pho*sis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/,
fr. <?/ to form anew; <?/ again + <?/ to form; <grk>morfh`</grk>
form.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Persp.)</fld> <def>A distorted or
monstrous projection or representation of an image on a plane or curved
surface, which, when viewed from a certain point, or as reflected from a
curved mirror or through a polyhedron, appears regular and in
proportion; a deformation of an image.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Anamorphism</er>,
2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A morbid or monstrous development,
or change of form, or degeneration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anamorphosy</ent>⟦br⟧
